<p>Le Claver camerounais est specialment adapté pour un  utilisation sur les appareis tactile comme un téléphone mobile ou une  tablette <span>Android</span> ou <span>iOS</span>. Vous pouvez utilisez le Clavier camerounais comme  n'importe quel autre clavier virtuel. Il faut noter que si vous branchez  ou connectez un clavier à l'appereil, le Clavier camerounais  fonctionnera comme un claver sur un ordinateur desktop ou portable.</p><h2>1 Mode d'emploi du clavier</h2>
<p>Le clavier camerounais fonctionne comme la plupart des  claviers Android ou iOS. Tapez sur une touche pour siasir la lettre  affichée. Appuyez longuement sur une touche marquée d'un point blanc  pour accéder aux caractères cachés.</p><img/><h2>2 Touches Speciaux</h2>
<p>Ou utilisez une touche spéciale pour accéder à d'autres  caractères !</p><img/><div><h2>3 Changez vers un autre clavier Keyman</h2><blockquote>Note : Si vous êtes plus familier avec la  disposition d'un clavier <span>AZERTY</span> , pensez à passer au  clavier Cameroun <span>AZERTY</span>.</blockquote></div><h2>4 Claviers Physiques</h2>
<p>***If you choose to connect a physical keyboard (i.e.  through Bluetooth or USB) to your mobile device, the physical keyboard  will respond like a desktop keyboard. See the Physical Keyboard Section  of this document for instructions and combinations.</p><blockquote>Note : Si vous êtes plus familier avec la  disposition d'un clavier <span>AZERTY</span> , pensez à passer au clavier Cameroun <span>AZERTY</span>.</blockquote><h2>5 Basculer entre differents claviers <span>non-Keyman</span></h2>
<p>Vous pouvez basculer entre différents claviers. Dans la  plupart des téléphones, le processus est le suivant:</p>
<ol>
<li>Cliquez dans une zone de texte pour faire afficher le  clavier.</li>
<li>Faites glisser le doigt du haut vers le bas.</li>
<li>Choisissez le bouton 'Sélectionner un clavier'.</li>
<li>Sélectionnez le clavier désiré.</li></ol></div></div><hr/>
<p>Le Clavier Camerounais est un produit de SIL Cameroun, © 2018. Pour  plus d´infos sur le Claver Camerounais ou la technologie linguistique au  Cameroun, veuillez visiter <a>https://langtechcameroon.info</a></p></div></div></div><!--Ending French--><!--Starting English--><div><a> Voir cette page en français...</a><div><img/><img/><h1>Cameroon <span>QWERTY</span>  Keyboard <span> for Keyman</span><br/>by SIL Cameroon</h1>
<p>Enabling you to type in your mother tongue!</p>
<p>Welcome to the <span><strong>Cameroon <span>QWERTY</span> Keyboard</strong></span> for Keyman. This page will  explain how to type in the vernacular languages of Cameroon using the Cameroon <span>QWERTY</span> Keyboard. </p>
<p>The <strong>Cameroon <span>QWERTY</span></strong> Keyboard, one of a set of <b>virtual keyboards</b>  maintained by the Language Technology team of <a>SIL  Cameroon</a>, allows you to type any languages that follow the <a>General Alphabet of Cameroonian  Languages</a>. The Ethnologue lists 279 living languages in Cameroon, and 275 of  these are indigenous. For a list of these languages, view <a>Cameroon in the  Ethnologue</a>.</p><hr/>
<p>To take advantage of the unique features of each device, the Cameroon  <span>QWERTY</span> Keyboard behaves  differently on physical keyboards and touch screens, please choose your interface  below:</p><!--Physical Keyboard--><div><input/><label>Physical Keyboard  (Windows, Mac, Linux, also Android and iOS with external keyboards) </label><div><div><h2>1 Physical Keyboards</h2>
<p>This section covers use of the Cameroon <span>QWERTY</span> with a physical  keyboard, harnessing the power of multiple fingers to type more  easily.</p><h2>2 Layout Overview</h2>
<p>Below is the layout of the Cameroon <span>QWERTY</span> Keyboard. Once you have  learned to use the <span>CAM</span> key and <span>Shift</span> keys, this image can be used as a quick  reference to find available characters.</p><img/><h2>3 Combinations</h2><img/>
<p>As shown above, each key on the Cameroon Keyboard can be  used to produce multiple characters (letters).</p>
<ol>
<li>If you tap the <span>E</span> key once,  you will get a lowercase "e".<br/>Sometimes you may need to use two  keys to get the letter you want. The SHIFT key is a key on a  computer keyboard. It is used to type capital letters (like this:  "ABC") instead of lowercase ("abc"). </li>
<li>If you hold the <span>Shift</span> key  and tap the <span>E</span> key once, you will get a  capital "E".<br/>The Cameroon Keyboard is special, and it is  possible to type other Characters not printed on your keyboard using  the "CAM" (Cameroon) key. On your Cameroon <span>QWERTY</span> Keyboard, the CAM  key is the <span>semicolon</span> key (<span>;</span>). Each time you need  the CAM key, just press <span>;</span>. To get the special characters shown  on the right side of each key in the chart (like this: "əɔɓ ")  instead of common characters (like "eob"), you need to use the CAM  key. </li>
<li>If you tap the <span>;</span> key once, and then press the <span>E</span> key, you will get schwa "ə". </li>
<li>If you tap the <span>;</span> key once, then hold <span>Shift</span> and type <span>E</span>, you will get capital schwa “Ə”.  <br/>In review, if you look at the keyboard chart, you’ll see  that most keys on the Cameroon keyboard can be used to produce up to  four different characters in this way. Use the chart to find the  letters you need for your language, and use a combination of <span>Shift</span> and the CAM Key (<span>;</span>) to  type them.</li>
<li>Unlike French, Cameroonian diacritics (accents) are  typed after the letter. For example, you would type: <span>;</span><span>e</span><span>'</span> to  get "ə̀"</li></ol><h2>4 Specific Keyboard Combination Details:</h2>
<p>Computers bought in different countries tend to have  different <strong>physical keyboard layouts</strong>. When using  <strong>virtual keyboards</strong>, it is MUCH easier to learn the  keyboard if the keys are <strong>in the same place</strong> as the  letters you want to type.</p>
<p>The Cameroon <span>QWERTY</span> keyboard is designed for computers with the following  physical keyboards:</p>
<ul>
<li>US English (QWERTY)</li>
<li>UK Engish (QWERTY)</li>
<li>Swiss French (QWERTZ)</li>
<li>German (QWERTZ)</li>
<li>Arabic 101 (Qwerty)</li></ul><blockquote>Note: If your computer has <span>an AZERTY</span> Keyboard or  something similar, consider removing Cameroon <span>QWERTY</span> and try the Cameroon  <span>AZERTY</span>  Keyboard</blockquote>
<p>The exact keys you need to press may vary slightly  depending on the physical keyboard on your machine. Choose the physical  keyboard layout on your computer below for more details:</p><!--US English Keyboard--><div><input/><label>United States English  Keyboard</label><div><div><h1>Combinations for Cameroon QWERTY based on physical en-us keyboard</h1><h2>Close Punctuation</h2><table><tr><td><span>  ')'</span></td><td><span>➜</span></td><td><span> ')'</span></td><td><span>RIGHT PARENTHESIS (U+0029)</span></td></tr><tr><td><span> [AltGr] + ']'</span></td><td><span>➜</span></td><td><span> ']'</span></td><td><span>RIGHT SQUARE BRACKET (U+005D)</span></td></tr><tr><td><span> [CAM Key] + ']'</span></td><td><span>➜</span></td><td><span> ']'</span></td><td><span>RIGHT SQUARE BRACKET (U+005D)</span></td></tr><tr><td><span> [AltGr] + '}'</span></td><td><span>➜</span></td><td><span> '}'</span></td><td><span>RIGHT CURLY BRACKET (U+007D)</span></td></tr><tr><td><span> [CAM Key]  '}'</span></td><td><span>➜</span></td><td><span> '}'</span></td><td><span>RIGHT CURLY BRACKET (U+007D)</span></td></tr></table><h2>Connector Punctuation</h2><table><tr><td><span>  '_'</span></td><td><span>➜</span></td><td><span> '_'</span></td><td><span>LOW LINE (U+005F)</span></td></tr></table><h2>Currency Symbol</h2><table><tr><td><span>  '$'</span></td><td><span>➜</span></td><td><span> '$'</span></td><td><span>DOLLAR SIGN (U+0024)</span></td></tr><tr><td><span> [AltGr] + '$'</span></td><td><span>➜</span></td><td><span> '€'</span></td><td><span>EURO SIGN (U+20AC)</span></td></tr><tr><td><span> [CAM Key]  '$'</span></td><td><span>➜</span></td><td><span> '€'</span></td><td><span>EURO SIGN (U+20AC)</span></td></tr></table><h2>Dash Punctuation</h2><table><tr><td><span>'-'</span></td><td><span>➜</span></td><td><span> '-'</span></td><td><span>HYPHEN-MINUS (U+002D)</span></td></tr><tr><td><span> [AltGr] + 'Q'</span></td><td><span>➜</span></td><td><span> '–'</span></td><td><span>EN DASH (U+2013)</span></td